    "longBusinessSummary": "Jazan Development and Investment Company, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the aquaculture, agricultural, manufacturing, and real estate businesses in Saudi Arabia and Egypt. It operates through Agricultural, Commercial, Shrimp Farming, and Investment Properties segments. It is involved in the cultivation of mangoes, aromatic plants, flowers, flower buds, grapes, figs, citrus fruits, pome and stone fruits including apples, apricots, cherries, peaches, pears, plums, ornamental plants, and nursery seedlings; marine shrimp farming; preservation of fish and fish products; cooling and freezing of fruits; production and bottling and distributing of pure filtered water; cutting, packing, and packaging fruits and vegetables; operation of hotels and heritage; and animal feed and food storage, as well as engages in the land transportation and refrigerated store activities. It also engages in the purchase, sale, and rental of land and real estate properties. The company was formerly known as Jazan Energy and Development Company. Jazan Development and Investment Company was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Jazan, Saudi Arabia.",
